Select a different folder to put the Citavi folder in, or correct the permissions on the Documents folder and try again.

data.name: UserDataFolderState_ExistsButCannotWrite
data.value:
Citavi startup cannot continue because Citavi could not write to the default folder for Citavi user files. This can occur because the folder is write-protected, or because you do not have rights to write in that folder. Citavi must be able to write to the folder to continue.
Select a different folder to put the Citavi folder in, or correct the permissions on the Documents folder and try again.

data.name: UserDataFolderState_InstallationSpecificUserDataFolderDoesNotExist
data.value:

Select a different folder for Citavi user files, or connect the disk or network share with the existing folder and try again.

data.name: UserDataFolderState_UnknownInstallation
data.value:
Citavi cannot start yet because Citavi has never been run from this location before. This can happen if: - You moved the Citavi program folder. - You installed Citavi to several locations on the same computer.
Select the folder for Citavi user files for this location of Citavi.

data.name: UserDataFolderState_UnknownState
data.value:
Citavi startup cannot continue because the folder for Citavi user files could not be found for an unknown reason.
Select the folder for Citavi user files.
